      "bodyEn": [
        "For Chinese herbal medicine to be most effective, you must decoct it yourself. (December 3, 2012, 17:23:45)",
        "First, let me share a case:",
        "Jiang XX, male, 56 years old. Initial visit on November 19, 2012:",
        "He reported that over ten days earlier, while caring for his hospitalized mother, he felt cold at night and distinctly felt a chill invade his back. In the following days, he developed pain in his back and shoulders. He had taken painkillers and used topical patches, but there was no improvement — in fact, there was a trend toward worsening. History of fatty liver. He came for consultation today.",
        "I looked: tongue was pale with a grayish-white coating. It was indeed due to external cold congealing in the channels and collaterals. The condition was not severe, so I wrote a prescription and told him to get three packs of herbs, saying these three packs should be enough to cure it. If he later wanted to address the fatty liver, that could be handled separately.",
        "When he returned the following Monday, I had expected the symptoms to have vanished or at least greatly diminished. Instead, the patient reported: the pain had not lessened at all.",
        "I asked how the herbs were decocted and how he took them. That's when I learned that, to avoid the trouble of decocting, he had asked the pharmacy to decoct them for him.",
        "I then said, \"Alright, here's what you do — take this same prescription, go home, and decoct it yourself. Give it another try.\"",
        "The following Monday he came back and said: \"Completely cured, no more pain!\" He requested to continue with treatment for the fatty liver.",
        "Pharmacy decoction uses a large machine — they put several packs' worth of herbs together and decoct them only once (note: only once!), then filter and package the liquid into multiple pouches, dispensing them as 2 or 3 doses per day. (This throws away two-thirds of your herbal potency, wastes two-thirds of your money, prolongs your treatment time, and lowers the doctor's professional reputation.)",
        "By contrast, the traditional method of decocting herbs yourself is: 1. Add water until it just covers the herbs (do not rinse the herbs). 2. Soak for 15-20 minutes, bring to a boil over high heat, then reduce to medium heat (do not cover the pot). Each decoction should be reduced to one small bowl (about 200 ml). 3. One pack of herbs needs to be decocted 2-3 times (taken 2-3 times). Take the herbs at least half an hour apart from meals.",
        "This is the standard decoction method for ordinary chronic conditions. Special cases require different methods, and the doctor will give additional instructions.",
        "From the surface it's clear: pharmacy decoction discards the equivalent of 1-2 decoctions' worth of medicine. This is, first, a waste of Chinese herbal resources; second, a significant financial loss for the patient; and third, it drastically reduces the therapeutic effect.",
        "Therefore, if you want to use Chinese herbal medicine to treat illness, you must not fear the trouble — you must decoct the herbs yourself."
      ]
