        "Synthesizing all the tongue, pulse, and symptom findings, this should be due to dryness-heat harassing the upper orifices, preventing the spirit and soul (Shen and Hun) from anchoring internally. The urgent priority was to clear fire, calm the spirit, and anchor the soul — to rescue the patient from over ten days of total sleeplessness. Other issues could be addressed later.",
        "Prescription: Chai Hu (Bupleurum), Zhi Zi (Gardenia), Huang Bai (Phellodendron), Chi Shao (Red Peony) and Bai Shao (White Peony), Sheng Mu Li (Raw Oyster Shell), Yu Jin (Curcuma), Huai Niu Xi (Achyranthes), Shan Yu Rou (Cornus), Mai Ya (Malt Sprout), Zhi Qiao (Bitter Orange), Gan Cao (Licorice). 7 packs.",
