        "December 21, 2012 — Third Visit: Bearing-down sensation in the lower abdomen still present (but much milder); the sacral region was noticeably more relaxed. Falling asleep normally, but would wake mid-sleep. Palpitations reduced. Belching and the sensation of esophageal blockage reduced.",
        "January 4, 2013 — Fourth Visit: Sleep normal; no more blockage sensation in the stomach or esophagus; sacral pain and heaviness gone. Essentially, symptoms in all areas had disappeared. She remarked with emotion that the previous full year of treatment had not matched the effect of these three weeks. She also brought in three fellow patients for consultation at the same time.",
        "After several months of persistent treatment, by July 12, 2013, she reported: none of the symptoms in any area had recurred. No more allergic reactions upon wind exposure; face no longer flushed with tidal heat or redness; nose no longer itchy or congested; lower abdomen no longer bearing down. Sleep was peaceful and stable. Lower back and legs no longer stiff.",
