        "May 8, 2011 — Phone follow-up: Has taken 5 doses of the above formula. Initially after taking it, bowel movements were watery, but energy improved with no fatigue. Currently stools are loose. Digestion of stool contents has improved compared to before. Stomach and liver region distension improved.",
        "May 13, 2011 — Second visit: Tongue tip red with slight stasis spots, yellow coating has resolved, thin sparse coating. Pulse slippery wiry rapid. Afternoon belching, gastric discomfort resolved, liver region still slightly uncomfortable but no longer painful or distended. Left eye no longer painful, but still has lacrimation.",
        "May 23, 2011 — Third visit: The patient felt the distance was too great and travel inconvenient, requesting a prescription by phone/SMS. The following information was transmitted at that time (four-diagnosis data collected by a physician at the local TCM hospital):",
        "Has belching, feels somewhat better after belching (this needs priority attention). Slight pressure sensation and discomfort in the right abdomen at umbilicus level. No upper abdominal distension or vomiting. Stool forms piles but is unformed, 1–2 times daily, no tenesmus. Slightly reduced flatulence. Urination normal. The patient is aware of a moist sensation in the eyes but without distension or pain, no lacrimation. No headache, dizziness, or fatigue. No dry mouth or cough. Sleep acceptable. Appetite normal. Pulse: wiry, thin, slippery. Tongue: pale red body, sparse coating, red and moist.",
        "June 1, 2011 — Fourth visit (four-diagnosis data collected by a physician at the local TCM hospital): Slight belching. Lower abdomen painful on moderate pressure; discomfort even without pressure. No upper abdominal distension or vomiting. Morning: stool forms piles but is unformed. Immediately after each of three meals: passes loose mushy stool, no tenesmus. Flatulence more frequent, gas odor has the same sour-smelly smell as the stool. Urination normal. Left eye has a sensation of discomfort but without distension or pain, no lacrimation. No headache, dizziness, or fatigue. No dry mouth or cough. Sleep acceptable with dreaming. Appetite normal. Pulse: wiry, slippery. Tongue: pale red body, thin yellow slightly greasy coating.",
        "June 23, 2011 — Fifth visit:",
