        "4. No bitter taste in the mouth upon waking, no halitosis or other oral odor. Body without other odors. Earwax is dry.",
        "5. No chest tightness, no palpitations.",
        "6. Diet normal, one bowl of rice per meal. No gastric distension after eating, no distension or pain in the rib-sides. No acid reflux, no stomach pain. Belching between 4–6 PM. Lower abdomen painful on moderate pressure, discomfort even without pressure; lower abdomen has a sensation of trapped gas. Not much flatulence.",
        "7. Bowel movements: Not dry. During medication: loose and unformed stools, no fewer than 4 bowel movements daily. During medication breaks: not loose, formed, or hard at the beginning and loose at the end, 1–2 bowel movements daily. Urine color: yellow when not drinking water for a while, clear with normal water intake, no foam. Urinates once during the night. No change in urination during medication compared to before. Sleep average, sometimes dreams.",
        "8. Falls asleep easily. Sleep depth varies between deep and light. Easily startled awake. Morning: head feels acceptable upon waking. Fatigue basically recovers after a night's sleep. No obvious sense of physical fatigue. No snoring during sleep.",
        "9. No sensation of lumbar soreness, heaviness, distension, pain, coldness, or aching. Legs feel sore and weak when climbing to the 6th or 7th floor. Hands and feet do not feel cold. Foot joints not painful. Palms and soles do not feel hot.",
        "10. In hot weather: body sweats profusely, easily sweats during sleep, sweats after slight daytime activity. No episodes of waves of heat, facial flushing followed by sweating, or palmar-plantar sweating.",
