        "Guo XX, male, 48 years old. First visit on 2013.6.14:",
        "Chief complaint: for the past 3 years, soreness, pain, and cold sensation in both arms and both sides of the neck. Over 3 years, failed to respond to treatment from specialists at multiple hospitals; now severe pain, unable to lift even a thermos of hot water with one hand; hands tremble when playing mahjong, dropping even a single mahjong tile from grasp. Neck pain disrupts sleep, causing vexation and irritability from the pain.",
        "Multiple hospital CT and other examinations ruled out cervical spine pathology. Heart rate 58-60 bpm. Asked whether he had overexerted himself. Answer: in recent years, due to business operations, had extensive worries and stress. Asked about history of cold or wind exposure. Answer: in recent years, only prolonged exposure to air conditioning in the car during summers. Physique robust on observation. Dizziness; sometimes a sensation of lost consciousness. Appetite good, bowel movements once every several days. Even now in summer, knee joints fear cold and wind at night. History of chronic pharyngitis; temperament irritable. Rarely dry mouth. Pale enlarged tongue with white coating, pulse deep-weak-moderate.",
