        "Zhao XX, female, 30 years old. First visit on 2013-6-28:",
        "Referred by an online TCM practitioner friend to see me in person. The background: this online TCM practitioner had previously treated a patient's pain condition for half a month with unsatisfactory results and could not identify the reason; he sought help in a TCM QQ group, where I adjusted his original prescription and the result was immediately effective, earning his admiration. The current patient was also treated by him online for some time with unsatisfactory results; since this patient happens to be in Beijing, he referred her to me for treatment.",
        "Reviewing the previous doctor's prescriptions, they mostly consisted of dampness-transforming, dampness-draining, or exterior-releasing and dampness-drying medicinals. The patient said the doctor diagnosed spleen dampness with phlegm-dampness obstruction.",
        "My first striking impression of the patient: her lips were pale and lusterless (inspection, the foremost of the four TCM examinations). Chief complaint: headache since childhood, severe chest tightness, especially during menstruation when she felt whole-body swelling (menses deep-colored and thick, cycle 25-26 days). Poor digestion.",
        "Present: chest tightness and shortness of breath, oppressive distension in the anterior and posterior chest. Difficulty falling asleep, shallow sleep, prone to anxiety. Fair appetite, frequent belching and acid reflux after meals. Bowel movement once every 1-2 days (sticky). Tongue edges covered with a full circle of tooth marks, body slightly purple with thin white coating; pulse deep-thready-weak.",
        "Pattern differentiation: heart and lung qi and blood deficiency, spleen and stomach transportation-insufficiency, clear orifices malnourished. Concurrently liver blood insufficiency with liver qi constraint.",
