        "2013.7.5 Second visit: completed 6 doses in one week; during the first 3 doses, bowel movements increased; after reading the blog article, she firmly believed in the treatment plan and continued taking the medicine. As a result, the last 3 doses did not increase bowel movements; stools normalized while urination frequency increased. Chest tightness in the cardiac region and back distension greatly improved, effect very evident. Essentially no headache for the week, but today had some headache due to not sleeping well yesterday from worries. Also recalled a symptom not mentioned at the previous visit: usually prone to nasal congestion, relieved by warmth. As well as numbness in the cardiac region and left arm. I explained that both symptoms are manifestations of heart-lung functional weakness, also corroborating the correctness of the previous diagnostic direction.",
