        "2012/5/30 Twelfth visit: hot flashes still slightly present; feet hot at night.",
        "2012/6/6 Thirteenth visit: feels all symptoms have disappeared; previous visual hallucinations also have not recurred. Wishes to stop medicine for a period to observe the effect.",
        "Hot flashes and sweating are commonly menopausal symptoms in women, but this patient, from around age 54 all the way to 63, still had such symptomatic responses because her five-organ yin deficiency was excessive, beyond that of ordinary people. Fortunately, after 3 months of regulation, the symptoms continuously improved to the point of essentially disappearing; particularly the visual hallucinations achieved an unexpectedly good outcome. Instruction: return after some time to continue regulation for consolidating the curative effect."
