      "bodyEn": [
        "Wang XX, female, 37 years old, from Shanxi Province. January 24, 2013.",
        "First visit.",
        "Chief complaint: In February 1992, small red spots appeared on the back (red, itchy). Subsequently diagnosed at a local tertiary hospital dermatology department as: psoriasis. Treated with Western medicine such as Tripterygium glycosides. It has now been over 20 years, with multiple treatments sought from various sources, yet it has repeatedly flared and worsened.",
        "Referred by a friend, she traveled to Beijing to seek my treatment. Current chief complaints: severe skin lesions on both legs and the waist, some also on the chest and back. The skin is red and itchy; the itching affects normal sleep.",
        "Lower legs feel heavy and distended. Palms feel hot. Bitter taste in the mouth. Drooling during sleep. Orbital distension during menstruation. Lacrimation in wind. Usually fatigued, low energy. Calves have a sensation of coldness. Menstruation arrives one week early.",
        "Tongue slightly dark crimson with thin sparse white coating. Pulse: right guan and chi positions weak, left chi position weak. At the time the patient herself rolled up her pant legs, revealing dense skin lesions covering the calves, connected into patches, with raised red plaques. (No local photos were taken at that time.)",
        "Pattern differentiation: Liver-kidney deficiency and damage, wind-toxin entering the blood.",
        "Prescription: Chaihu, Danshen, Baishao, Chishao, Huainiuxi, Duan Longgu, Zhimu, Tufuling, Baixianpi, Huangbai, Fangfeng, Qianghuo, Cangzhu, Gancao. 10 doses. She returned to Shanxi to take the medication.",
        "On February 17, 2013, she sent a photo of the left knee area. (This photo shows the result after half a month of medication; the initial actual condition would have been even more severe than what the photo shows.)",
        "March 7, 2013.",
        "Second visit: Has taken a total of 16 doses of the above formula. Rolling up the pant legs, the erythematous lesions on the calves were visibly reduced, with fewer raised areas. She reported that from the 10th day onward bowel movements increased to 3 times daily. Skin itching reduced. Hair loss reduced. Menstruation this time was only 2 days early (previously 7–8 days early).",
        "April 11, 2013.",
        "Third visit: After 13 doses of the second-visit formula. Daytime drowsiness, facial complexion pale yellow, daytime sleepiness. Leg lesion pigmentation markedly reduced. Scattered red spots on upper limbs clearly visible in color. Bowel movements 1–2 times daily. Palms hot. Menstrual flow scant. Skin itching basically absent; only occasional mild itching at night.",
        "On July 9, 2013, I left her a message on QQ asking: To what degree has the skin improved?",
        "She answered: \"Hello, Dr. Yuan. I saw your text message. Thank you for your care and concern. Regarding my condition, it has improved considerably since my last visit to Beijing. The skin on my legs overall looks whiter than before, and new rashes appear less frequently. However, it is still quite dry, and my lower legs feel somewhat distended when I'm tired. As for other aspects, there is no obvious difference from before. Appetite and sleep are fine. The reason I haven't come for a follow-up on time is that my workplace is undergoing a major structural reform recently, and this time... so it's really not convenient to ask for leave during this period. Otherwise I would have come to see you already. As for photos of the progress, I'll take them tomorrow and send them to you. Thank you again, Dr. Yuan, for your concern.\"",
        "August 1, 2013.",
        "Came to Beijing for follow-up: Skin basically normal. Some scattered dark residual marks can still be seen beneath the skin. The previously chronic heavy sensation in the legs is now gone. Energy is abundant. No lumbar soreness, no abdominal distension, etc. Appetite good, sleep acceptable. No more sleep disruption from skin itching. In July, due to busy work, she stopped medication for half a month, yet the skin did not relapse — remained very stable. When she later resumed medication, the skin again showed some small scattered red spots, which then subsequently faded in turn. Menstruation is now delayed by 2–3 days (previously 7–8 days early). She feels her current energy is much better than before treatment.",
        "October 10, 2013.",
        "Came to Beijing for follow-up: The skin of the entire body normally shows no lesions or rashes. Only brief, transient appearances during menstruation, and only in small amounts at indeterminate sites among three areas — shoulders, elbows, and calves — and the skin no longer itches.",
        "The chronic heavy, distended, and painful sensation in the legs, which had never resolved despite years of treatment from many sources, has now not recurred. The body feels light. Menstrual cramps have also disappeared, as have the previous lumbar soreness and dry eyes during menstruation. Overall physical constitution keeps strengthening.",
        "Because this patient has suffered from the disease for a very long time, the psychological pressure on her was immense. Living in Shanxi, each long-distance trip to Beijing for a follow-up was not easy, so every time I was especially meticulous in extracting information about her condition before and after medication, along with the four-diagnosis data. Both sides communicated deeply about the condition, and as a result, the treatment outcome was also very satisfactory."
      ]
