        "Thank You Letter",
        "I am a patient surnamed Che from Weihai, Shandong. For over 20 years I have suffered from dermatitis, with scattered coin-sized psoriatic plaques on my legs. When upset or after eating spicy or irritating foods, pimples would appear on my face, and on my scalp",
        "there were also multiple stubborn psoriatic plaques, often unbearably itchy. Over the years I tried many treatments to no avail — it was always one wave not yet settled before another rose. The plaques on my scalp in particular produced a lot of dandruff, which affected both appearance and caused great",
        "discomfort. To relieve symptoms, I tried corticosteroid medications like Pikangwang (Clotrimazole/Betamethasone cream). At first the effects were dramatic, but after just a few days the condition would recur. Because there was still some effect and temporary relief, I gradually developed a habit of",
        "applying this type of hormonal cream whenever I itched, and after over ten years I could not stop.",
        "By chance, I met Dr. Yuan in Beijing. By this point I already had deep steroid-dependent dermatitis, made worse by internal heat. Facial pigmentation was severe, and both the epidermis and dermis had thinned under long-term medication stimulation, with visible",
