        "From the initial consultation on September 3, 2017, to the examination on October 6 — exactly one month of treatment — the tumor measured 67 × 64 mm. Comparing this data with the August 26 examination report, when the tumor was 75 × 65 mm, it is now smaller. (The doctor's note of 'slightly enlarged compared to prior' was comparing with the June scan.) In other words, the actual size is now markedly smaller than on August 26. Moreover, the report noted that 'the above-described mixed mass shows no obvious blood flow signal,' which indirectly suggests the tumor has lost its blood supply and has lost vitality.",
