        "Zhang XX, male, 68 years old,",
        "2017.1.31 Initial visit:",
        "This elderly man was brought to my home for consultation by his son (whose gastric disease I had treated a few years earlier) during the Spring Festival holiday, before I had officially resumed clinic work — I gave a prescription for him to purchase medicine elsewhere. The dry eye syndrome was extremely severe. During the visit, he blinked almost every second — blinking incessantly. His eyes were dry, painful, and unbearably uncomfortable; he could not help but blink. He reported suffering from dry eye syndrome for over 2 years. It felt somewhat better at night and worse during the day. Upon waking each day, he noticed copious eye discharge. In his youth, he drank alcohol heavily. His face was flushed (he had also drunk alcohol on the day of the visit). Sometimes bitter taste in the mouth. Tongue pale with thin white coating, slightly yellow and greasy at the posterior root. Pulse slippery and rapid. History of hypoglycemia and joint pain.",
