      "hasReports": false,
      "body": [
        "小孩不自主地挤眉弄眼、吐舌、面部抽动，中医归为肝风，这在小儿病中时常有遇到。",
        "这病说起来理论很简单，看十位中医，十位都会这样定，但真对病情能治疗达到理想效果的医生可不多。因在病理发展过程中往往不是单纯的这点肝风内动，而大多同时都兼有其他问题，从而导致医生对该病的综合判断困难，在治疗过程中也就不易见效，甚至这个问题没有治好，反而在用药过程中导致新的病变产生。",
        "前不久就有一位父亲带一6岁的男孩来我这治疗这病，孩子平常比同龄人明显多动反应，有“多动症”的表现，而且面部的眼、嘴角、鼻翼不自主的抽动。",
        "开始去医院治疗，发现在治疗一段时间后舌苔越来变厚腻了，本来平时食欲、大便都不正常。原来的问题没有得到解决，还新增了问题。这父亲自己也学了些中医知识，怀疑治疗方案不对劲。",
        "其实这孩子的问题就如我上面讲的那样，本来是肝风内动，这判断没有错，医院的医生也是这样判断的，也是这样对证治疗的，总方向来说没有错，可就是因为孩子不仅仅是肝风内动，而同时兼有其他方面的问题（这孩子脾胃弱），其体质当前不适用平熄肝风的药来对抗性处理，所以吃药后不但没有缓解原来的问题，反而新增了问题。好在父亲懂些中医知识，知道不能继续这个方案了，立即中止了治疗，于是前来向我咨询其理。我告诉他，孩子本身脾胃弱，承受不了当前的清热平肝之品的药力，所以才出现了上述问题。",
        "在治疗所有慢性病的过程中，如果仅仅是单纯地以某病用某药某方机械式地治疗，必然效果不理想，甚至造成不良反应。而中医的长项就在于“整体观、辩证施治”，就是说不要只看到局部这点问题，应该将身体各方面的问题都要看清楚，特别是与当前疾病有直接或间接联系的部分，在决定治疗方案中是必须要考虑进去的。这样才能达到治疗过程中，原来的病情在不断好转，其他方面对当前疾病有影响的方面也能得到解决，最终让疾病的各方面都得到向好的方向转化的趋势，直到治愈。",
        "这孩子在我这吃了一周药，于2017年3月4日二诊时，其父亲反馈：“孩子现在食欲转好。大便成形，大便比原来好多了”。原来舌苔的厚腻也明显的转薄而化开了。原来夜晚睡觉中有不安稳、吼叫的反应，现在也睡得安稳了。虽然面部的抽动还没有明显改善，但从睡眠反应上已明显得到了改善，胃肠功能得到提升了，这些方面都已可判断为“整体病情”在向好的方向转化。因为仅仅刚吃一周的药，所以有此效果已让人满意了。",
        "一直每周坚持复诊一次，今日（4月2日）孩子的父亲来反馈：面部抽动反应已基本消失，今日已随母亲借清明假期回老家去玩。",
        "叮嘱：假期后回京还应坚持复诊以巩固疗效。"
      ],
      "images": [
        "img/case_117_1.png"
      ],
      "bodyEn": [
        "Involuntary blinking, eye rolling, tongue protrusion, and facial twitching in children are classified in TCM as liver wind. This is encountered fairly often in pediatric conditions.",
        "The theory behind this condition sounds simple — ask ten TCM practitioners and all ten would make the same diagnosis. But there are not many physicians who can actually achieve ideal treatment results for this condition. This is because during the pathological progression, it is often not simply a matter of liver wind stirring internally. Most cases simultaneously involve other problems, making comprehensive clinical judgment difficult for the physician, and thus treatment is often ineffective. In some cases, not only does the original problem fail to resolve, but the medication may even induce new pathological changes.",
        "Not long ago, a father brought his 6-year-old boy to me for treatment of this condition. The child was noticeably more hyperactive than peers, displaying signs of \"ADHD,\" with involuntary twitching of the eyes, corners of the mouth, and nasal alae.",
        "Initially, they sought treatment at a hospital. It was discovered that after a period of treatment, the tongue coating became increasingly thick and greasy. Originally, the child's appetite and bowel movements had been abnormal. The original problem was not resolved, and new problems were added. The father, who had studied some TCM knowledge himself, suspected something was wrong with the treatment protocol.",
        "In fact, this child's problem was exactly as I described above. The diagnosis of liver wind stirring internally was correct, and the hospital physicians made the same diagnosis and treated accordingly. In terms of the general direction, there was no mistake. However, because the child did not merely have liver wind stirring internally but simultaneously had problems in other aspects (this child had a weak spleen and stomach), the child's constitution at that time could not tolerate the counteracting approach of using liver-wind-calming medicinals. Therefore, after taking the medicine, not only did the original problem not improve, but new problems emerged. Fortunately, the father understood some TCM knowledge and knew not to continue this protocol, so he immediately stopped the treatment and came to consult me about the reasoning. I told him that the child's spleen and stomach were inherently weak and could not withstand the potency of heat-clearing, liver-calming medicinals, which was why the above problems occurred.",
        "In treating all chronic diseases, if one simply treats a disease mechanically with a specific formula for a specific disease, the results will inevitably be unsatisfactory and may even cause adverse reactions. The strength of TCM lies precisely in its \"holistic perspective and pattern-differentiated treatment.\" This means one must not only look at the local problem but must clearly see all aspects of the body's condition — especially those parts that have a direct or indirect connection with the current disease. These must be taken into account when deciding the treatment plan. Only in this way can the original condition continuously improve during treatment while other aspects that influence the current disease are also resolved, ultimately bringing about a trend of improvement in all aspects of the disease until complete recovery.",
        "This child took medicine with me for one week. At the second visit on March 4, 2017, the father reported: \"The child's appetite has improved now. Stools are formed, much better than before.\" The previously thick, greasy tongue coating had also clearly thinned and resolved. The restlessness and shouting during nighttime sleep that had occurred before had also subsided — now the child slept peacefully. Although the facial twitching had not yet shown significant improvement, the sleep response had clearly improved and gastrointestinal function had been enhanced. These aspects could already be judged as indicating that the \"overall condition\" was transforming in a positive direction. Having taken medicine for only one week, these results were already satisfying.",
        "The child consistently came for follow-up once a week. Today (April 2), the father came to report: The facial twitching had basically disappeared. Today, the child had returned to the hometown with his mother to enjoy the Qingming Festival holiday.",
        "Instructions: After returning to Beijing following the holiday, continue follow-up consultations to consolidate the therapeutic effect."
      ]
