      "bodyEn": [
        "Cao XX, female, 39 years old, from Tangshan, Hebei. 2017.1.21",
        "Initial visit:",
        "She reported: On New Year's Day this year, she developed a cold with fever lasting 3 days, followed by a cough that had not resolved to date. In the interim, she had sought treatment from a TCM practitioner at a local hospital, but the results were unsatisfactory. (Family members are TCM enthusiasts and had also prescribed formulas on their own to treat her. Looking at both the hospital prescription and the self-formulated prescription, neither matched the pattern.)",
        "In 2016, she had come to me for treatment of severe breast nodular hyperplasia (pain so intense she could not sleep normally) and was cured — she has been fine ever since. Therefore, she now made a special trip from Tangshan to Beijing for consultation and treatment of the cough.",
        "Currently coughing, worse at night and milder during the day. Regardless of day or night, occasional sudden throat itching would trigger paroxysmal coughing. White sputum. Gastric distension and fullness. Belching. Appetite acceptable. Bowel movements once every 2 days (long-term pattern). Long-term constitutional weakness, cold intolerance, low blood pressure. Tongue pale with white coating, slightly greasy in the center and thin and slippery at the edges. Pulse weak.",
        "Pattern differentiation: Wind damage (with deficiency-cold) cough",
        "Prescription: Mimalhuang, Xingren, Fabanxia, Zisu, Fangfeng, Houpo, Muxiang, Cangzhu, Chenpi, Fuling, Beishashen, Danshen, Danggui, Gancao",
        "Seven doses",
        "2017.2.4",
        "Second visit: Cough markedly reduced. Now occasional cough (scanty sputum), mild sore throat, occasional gastric distension. Appetite acceptable. Bowel movements once every 2 days. Tongue pale with slightly dry coating, thin white slightly yellow. Pulse weak.",
        "2017.2.11",
        "Third visit: Cough completely resolved. No more sore throat. No more gastric distension. Bowel movements once daily. Occasional belching.",
        "Self-palpation revealed tenderness around the umbilicus. Had suffered intestinal obstruction twice in recent years. History of hemorrhoids. History of cold hands and feet.",
        "After the previous two treatment courses, the cough was resolved. This visit focused on regulating constitutional deficiency-cold issues."
      ]
