        "Dong XX, male, 37 years old, knee joint swelling and pain.",
        "2015.5.3, first visit:",
        "The patient came saying he was referred by a colleague, who had also been treated here previously for gout.",
        "Reports persistently elevated uric acid for over 5 years. First manifested as heel pain, then pain extended to the lower leg. By 2012, knee joint problems had appeared. Hospital diagnosed knee synovitis. Now the left knee is severely painful and the condition is spreading to the right knee. Walking is difficult; uses two crutches to get around. Dull yellow complexion without luster, acne on the forehead, anxious, heavy work stress. Hair has been graying over the past 5 years. Body fatigue, lower back soreness and heaviness, excessive sweating. Previously consulted a TCM practitioner who said dampness was severe, so he has been eating coix seed porridge frequently for the past 2 years, but uric acid remains high. Bowel movements once daily, sleep and appetite are okay. Tongue pale red with little coating, pulse deep and weak.",
        "Diagnosis: Liver-kidney yin deficiency, combined with qi deficiency.",
        "Prescription: Guizhi (Cinnamon Twig), Baishao (White Peony), Danggui (Angelica), Chuanxiong (Sichuan Lovage), Shengdi (Rehmannia), Duzhong (Eucommia), Jisheng (Taxillus), Huainiuxi (Achyranthes), Zexie (Alisma).",
