        "2015.5.24, third visit: Knee joint is no longer swollen or painful, just still feels somewhat stiff when walking, no other discomfort. Bowel movements normal, once daily.",
        "2015.5.31, fourth visit: Knee joint normal, walking normal, complexion has normalized.",
        "Both the patient and family feel the results are remarkable. His wife has also started taking Chinese herbal medicine to regulate her body. Their daughter, just a few years old, has had an allergic constitution for several years — allergic to wheat flour etc., urticaria and nosebleeds. After 2 weeks of medicine, she then went out for one week.",
        "On June 21, came to follow-up and reported that allergies had not recurred, and nosebleeds had no reaction either. Previously, allergies and nosebleeds would recur every two or three days, and she had never stopped taking Western or Chinese medicine. They asked me why treatment at other hospitals never produced results.",
