      "title": "对一些有过敏体质的人，在吃中药时，一定要注意忌口问题",
      "titleEn": "For People With Allergic Constitution — Dietary Restrictions Are Critical When Taking Chinese Herbs",
      "tags": [
        "skin"
      ],
      "hasReports": true,
      "body": [
        "过敏反应一例",
        "李XX，女，33岁，2014/7/18",
        "经朋友介绍来调理“亚健康”问题。",
        "自述：白天肩、四肢酸软、身体常有困倦，大多数日子夜里入睡困难。身体怕凉（冬天明显），平时手心热汗（扪之烫手），前些时出现过手背湿疹、头顶生小痘。饭后有胃胀感，偶尔出现气短，易咽痛（上火）。月经周期28天，量少而暗。大便稀，日行1-2次。舌边齿状，淡红而少苔。脉沉弱。",
        "辩证：脾肺气虚、肝肾不足，少兼湿热上火。",
        "处方：党参 白术 焦山楂 炒麦芽 山茱萸 煅龙骨 香附 木香 黄芩 菖蒲 酸枣仁 甘草",
        "七副。",
        "当晚发来消息，说出现过敏反应，并传来图片。",
        "我一看，吓一跳，连忙翻看病案记录查看，查看每一味药，脑子里搜索”过敏类药品名称”，没有看出处方中有致敏类的药物。虽然如此，也不敢轻视，告诉患者，“从表现症状看，确实是过敏反应，需要立即做相关处理(告诉了她一些具体的处理方法)，同时立即停止服中药。现在无法确定过敏源是什么，也无法确定或排出是不是服中药致敏，只能等过敏症状消失后，再少量试服中药，才能确定。后面如有问题再与我联系”。",
        "一周后复诊，自述上次过敏反应二天后就没事了，并再服中药也没有再出现过敏反应。同时反馈：经这一周的服药，睡眠质量得到了明显的改善，身体一下就感觉轻松了许多，不象原来那样整天疲倦了。",
        "我寻问后得知在上次就诊当天晚上，与同学一起聚会，吃过卤鸭脖等发性食物。",
        "过敏问题的根源找到了，就是她这类素有过敏反应体质的人，平时很容易因饮食一些发性食品而出现过敏反应。所以，对易过敏反应的患者，一定要注意饮食禁忌，医生叮嘱的一些不能吃的发性食物一定要做到忌口，否则出现过敏反应，还以为是中药有问题，引来不必要的麻烦，导致治疗不顺利。"
      ],
      "images": [
        "img/case_155_1.jpg",
        "img/case_155_2.jpg"
      ],
      "bodyEn": [
        "A case of allergic reaction.",
        "Li XX, female, 33 years old. July 18, 2014.",
        "She came on a friend's recommendation to address a 'sub-health' condition.",
        "She reported: During the day, her shoulders and all four limbs were sore, weak, and listless, and her body frequently felt fatigued. On most nights she had difficulty falling asleep. Her body was averse to cold (pronounced in winter). Her palms were usually hot and sweaty (hot to the touch). Some time earlier she had experienced eczema on the back of the hands and small pimples on the crown of the head. After meals she felt stomach distension, occasionally experienced shortness of breath, and was prone to sore throat (heat rising). Her menstrual cycle was 28 days, with scant, dark flow. Stools were loose, once or twice daily. The tongue edges showed teeth marks; the tongue body was pale red with scant coating. The pulse was deep and weak.",
        "Pattern differentiation: Spleen-Lung qi deficiency; Liver-Kidney insufficiency, with a mild component of damp-heat causing upward heat.",
        "Prescription: Dang Shen (Codonopsis), Bai Zhu (Atractylodes Macrocephala), Jiao Shan Zha (Crataegus-charred), Chao Mai Ya (Hordei Germinatus-dry-fried), Shan Zhu Yu (Cornus), Duan Long Gu (Fossilized Bone-calcined), Xiang Fu (Cyperus), Mu Xiang (Aucklandia), Huang Qin (Scutellaria), Chang Pu (Acorus), Suan Zao Ren (Ziziphus Spinosa), Gan Cao (Licorice).",
        "Seven doses.",
        "That evening she sent a message saying she had developed an allergic reaction and transmitted a photo.",
        "I was alarmed upon seeing it and hurriedly reviewed the case record, examining each individual herb and searching my memory for 'allergenic drug categories.' I could not identify any allergen-triggering herb in the prescription. Nevertheless, I took it seriously and told the patient, 'Based on the presenting symptoms, this does appear to be an allergic reaction. You need to take the relevant measures immediately (I instructed her on specific management steps), and at the same time stop taking the Chinese herbs at once. Right now we cannot determine what the allergen is, nor can we confirm or rule out whether the herbal medicine caused the allergy. We can only wait until the allergic symptoms have subsided, then try a small test dose of the herbs to confirm. If problems arise later, contact me again.'",
        "She returned for a follow-up one week later and reported that the allergic reaction had resolved after two days, and when she resumed the herbs no further allergic reaction occurred. She also reported: After this week of taking the medicine, her sleep quality had markedly improved, her body suddenly felt much lighter and more relaxed, and she was no longer tired all day as she had been before.",
        "Upon further questioning, I learned that on the evening of her initial consultation she had attended a classmate gathering and eaten stimulating foods such as braised duck neck.",
        "The root cause of the allergic issue was thus identified: people like her who have a constitution predisposed to allergic reactions are very prone to develop allergic symptoms after consuming certain stimulating foods. Therefore, patients who are susceptible to allergic reactions must strictly observe dietary restrictions. Any stimulating foods that the physician warns against must be avoided entirely. Otherwise, if an allergic reaction occurs, the patient may mistakenly assume the Chinese herbs are the problem, leading to unnecessary complications and disrupting the course of treatment."
      ]
