        "The treatment approach for chronic stomach diseases differs greatly from that for acute ones. Acute stomach conditions emphasize clearing inflammation, whereas chronic stomach conditions emphasize nourishing the stomach, soothing the liver, and supplementing the spleen and kidneys. One should not overuse or heavily rely on bitter-cold anti-inflammatory medicinals. The focus is on strengthening gastric function, which ultimately allows these chronic inflammations and local lesions to be eliminated and repaired.",
