      "hasReports": false,
      "body": [
        "余XX，女，79岁。2012。元。10日初诊：",
        "北京某医院诊断书：“宫颈癌1B1期，阴道后壁膨出，中度。阴道不规则出血6个月。宫颈见外生菜花样肿物，直径2cm，质硬。”经医院中、西医治疗6个月，阴道出血现象一直未停。",
        "观以前医院的中药处方多按气不固血处治，病人自觉服医院中药后，每次出血量有所减少，但每天一直没有停止过出血。",
        "现症状：睡眠极差，腰疼，乏力（感觉累，有冠心病史），脚趾发热（夜间重）；盗汗、白天动则出汗，食后腹胀，食后即要大便，大便时感觉坠胀，每次大便时即从阴道滴沥出血。面浮肿、脚肿。舌光少苔，脉沉弱",
        "此为阴虚血热、毒郁，先调整阴阳平衡为先，希望能让身体整体症状得到改善，让身体素质提高，再最终达到增强身体的抗癌能力。",
        "处方：柴胡 白芍 生地",
        "桑葚五味紫草乌梅煅龙牡酸枣仁白术 茯苓 党参 鸡内金 地榆炭 甘草",
        "嘱先试服3付，效果好再服继续按方服用至春节后再复诊。",
        "次日来电话反馈：大便时阴道出血量比以往明显增多，问如何处理？（这是本人没有预想到的结果）想到病情诊断应该没有错啊，为何服药后反而病情增重呢？嘱病人：“如果担心的话就暂停中药，观察后面反应，如果后面反应有好转就继续服药，如果症状还是加重就停止用药，还是上医院处理，不要延误病情。”",
        "此病人后面说因家境困难，当时取了3付药，又不忍心丢弃未服的另2付中药，加上前面诊断时给她讲解的病理情况感觉很有道理，就下决心吃完3付再另作打算。",
        "2012。1。20日电话反馈：到今日为止共服了10付药，从服第二付时，大便时就未再出现阴道出血症状，而且整体各方面症状都在改善：夜间盗汗没有了，白天动后出汗也减轻了，食后腹胀有所减轻，面部、脚部肿减轻，大便时坠胀感没有了，脚趾发烧感在近三天也消失了。还有口舌干感觉，腹胀感觉。大便排泄量增多（多时达日行10来次，便后有乏力感）。全家人见此效果，皆大欢喜，开心过年。",
        "电话回复嘱：各方面症状改善，说明药已对证。大便增多为排毒的好现象，可以减少服药量，减少大便次数，让大便每日3-4次为宜。坚持服药到春节后复诊。",
        "2012.2.7",
        "二诊：自述一家人春节过得开心，妇科方面的出血从上次服药后到现在一直未在发生，很稳定。腰不疼了，夜间也不出汗了。饮食、大便、睡眠正常了。前几日因感冒，现有些咳嗽、痰白、腿肿、腹胀、心慌。请求给予继续服中药调理。",
        "过了数月，患者儿子带一病友来看病，同时反馈：其母亲感觉身体稳定了，年岁已高，要求回老家休息。回老家后一直坚持用我给开的处方服中药，身体一直很稳定，未再出现不适症状。"
      ],
      "bodyEn": [
        "Yu XX, female, 79 years old. First visit: January 10, 2012.",
        "Diagnosis from a Beijing hospital: \"Cervical cancer stage 1B1, posterior vaginal wall prolapse, moderate. Irregular vaginal bleeding for 6 months. An exophytic cauliflower-like mass visible on the cervix, 2 cm in diameter, hard in texture.\" After 6 months of combined Chinese and Western medical treatment at the hospital, the vaginal bleeding had never stopped.",
        "Reviewing the hospital's previous herbal prescriptions, most were based on treating qi failing to secure the blood. The patient herself felt that after taking the hospital's herbal medicine, the amount of bleeding decreased somewhat each time, but it had never stopped completely on any day.",
        "Current symptoms: extremely poor sleep, lower back pain, fatigue (feeling tired, history of coronary heart disease), burning sensation in the toes (worse at night); night sweats, sweating on slight daytime exertion, postprandial abdominal distension, urge to defecate immediately after eating, bearing-down and distending sensation during defecation; each bowel movement accompanied by dripping vaginal bleeding. Facial edema, foot edema. Glossy tongue with scant coating, deep-weak pulse.",
        "This was diagnosed as yin deficiency with blood heat and toxin stagnation. The priority was to adjust the yin-yang balance first, in the hope of improving the overall symptoms, strengthening the constitution, and ultimately enhancing the body's anti-cancer capacity.",
        "Prescription: Chai Hu (Bupleurum), Bai Shao (White Peony Root), Sheng Di (Raw Rehmannia Root),",
        "Sang Shen (Mulberry Fruit), Wu Wei Zi (Schisandra Fruit), Zi Cao (Arnebia Root), Wu Mei (Mume Fruit), Duan Long Gu (Calcined Dragon Bone), Duan Mu Li (Calcined Oyster Shell), Suan Zao Ren (Jujube Seed), Bai Zhu (Atractylodes Rhizome), Fu Ling (Poria), Dang Shen (Codonopsis Root), Ji Nei Jin (Chicken Gizzard Lining), Di Yu Tan (Charred Sanguisorba Root), Gan Cao (Licorice).",
        "Advised to try 3 doses first; if the effect was good, continue the prescription and return for follow-up after the Spring Festival.",
        "The next day, phone feedback: the amount of vaginal bleeding during bowel movements had markedly increased compared to before. Asked: how to handle this? (This was a result I had not anticipated.) I reflected that the disease pattern diagnosis should not have been wrong — why did the condition worsen after taking the medicine? Advised the patient: \"If you are worried, pause the herbal medicine for now and observe the subsequent response. If the response improves, continue the medication. If symptoms continue to worsen, stop the medication and go to the hospital; do not delay treatment.\"",
        "The patient later said that, due to financial hardship, she had only picked up 3 doses that time. Unwilling to discard the remaining 2 doses, and feeling that my explanation of the pathology during the diagnosis made good sense, she resolved to finish all 3 doses and then reassess.",
        "January 20, 2012, phone feedback: to date she had taken a total of 10 doses. From the second dose onward, vaginal bleeding during bowel movements had stopped, and all aspects of her symptoms had improved: night sweats gone, daytime exertional sweating reduced, postprandial abdominal distension reduced, facial and foot edema reduced, bearing-down and distending sensation during defecation gone, burning sensation in the toes had also disappeared in the past three days. There was still a dry sensation in the mouth and tongue, and some abdominal distension. Stool volume had markedly increased (sometimes up to 10 bowel movements per day, with fatigue afterwards). The entire family was delighted at the results and celebrated the New Year happily.",
        "Phone instructions: Since all aspects of symptoms had improved, this indicated the medicine was correctly matched to the pattern. The increased bowel movements were a good sign of toxin elimination. Reduce the dosage to decrease bowel movement frequency, aiming for 3–4 times daily. Continue taking the medicine and return for follow-up after the Spring Festival.",
        "February 7, 2012",
        "Second visit: Patient reported that the family had a happy Spring Festival. The gynecological bleeding had not recurred since the last round of medication and remained stable. Lower back pain gone. No more night sweats. Appetite, bowel movements, and sleep were normal. A few days earlier she had caught a cold, and currently had some coughing with white sputum, leg edema, abdominal distension, and palpitations. Requested to continue herbal treatment.",
        "Several months later, the patient's son brought a fellow patient for consultation, and also reported: his mother felt her condition had stabilized. Being advanced in age, she had asked to return to her hometown to rest. After returning home, she had consistently continued taking the herbal formula I prescribed, and her condition had remained stable, with no recurrence of discomfort."
      ]
