        "On June 10, 2011, he was brought to see me by a friend. Standing over 1.7 meters tall, he weighed more than 200 jin, and his weight had been rising steadily in recent months. On the medial aspect of his right calf, there was a patch of black-purple necrotic skin roughly the size of two palms (deep vein thrombosis for over four years; it had once continuously oozed pus before healing). The forefoot and toes of his left foot had been surgically removed due to trauma.",
