        "On February 22, 2010, he reported via QQ: \"My eyes are much better now — no more pain. The shoulder pain I used to have is also gone now.\"",
        "Second visit on June 25, 2010: The white tongue coating had receded. Bowel movements were 1–2 times per day and basically formed. Various aspects had improved, though his eyes still felt distended and his lower back and shoulders were slightly sore.",
        "Because of the long history of this illness, his symptoms did occasionally relapse due to dietary indiscretions, colds, overwork, and other factors during the treatment course. However, the patient felt that the results of the treatment he received here were far better than anywhere else he had been, so he persisted with the treatment throughout. By 2011, the total treatment period (including intermittent breaks) had reached roughly one year.",
        "At present, his spleen, kidneys, gallbladder, stomach, and intestines have been regulated to a relatively stable state of balance. His bowel movements are normal, his complexion is ruddy, his mental state is good, and he is able to live and work normally."
