        "Irregular menstruation for many years since menarche after puberty; flooding and spotting (beng lou) for several years. After coming to Guangzhou, 5 years of delayed irregular menstruation (mostly 40–50 days); sometimes flooding and spotting requiring hemostatic drugs; pulling pain in the left lower abdomen 5–7 days before or after menstruation; this time, lower abdominal pain starting 3 days before menstruation, relieved after bowel movement or passing gas; abdominal pain 1–2 days before menstruation, lower abdomen and buttocks icy cold, with blood clots; sometimes menstrual spotting that drags on for over ten days. Leukorrhea yellow or yellow-green, foul-smelling, sometimes tofu-residue-like milky white, accompanied by itching.",
